CERN OPEN HARDWARE LICENCE

Version 2 - Strongly Reciprocal

1. Definitions

“Licence” means this CERN Open Hardware Licence.

“Licensor” means the individual or legal entity offering the Source under
the terms of this Licence.

“You” (or “Your”) means an individual or a legal entity exercising rights
under this Licence.

“Source” means the information necessary to describe, design, make,
manufacture, test or prepare Products, including but not limited to
schematics, designs, drawings, CAD files, PCB layouts, bills of materials,
firmware, documentation, and other related materials.

“Product” means any device, component, or system whose design is described
by the Source.

“Modify” means to alter, transform, or build upon the Source.

2. Licence Grant

The Licensor hereby grants You a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive
licence to use, reproduce, modify, distribute, and make Products based on
the Source, subject to the terms and conditions of this Licence.

3. Source Availability (Strong Reciprocity)

If You distribute the Source, or a Product based on the Source, You must
make the complete corresponding Source available under this Licence.

Any Modified Source must be licensed under the same CERN-OHL-S v2.

4. Distribution of Products

If You distribute Products, You must:
a) Provide recipients with information on how to obtain the Source
b) Ensure that the Source is available under this Licence
c) Include a copy of this Licence with the Product or its documentation

5. Attribution

You must retain all copyright, licence notices, and attributions included
in the Source.

6. Disclaimer of Warranty

THE SOURCE IS PROVIDED “AS IS” AND WITHOUT ANY EXPRESS OR IMPLIED WARRANTY,
INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A
PARTICULAR PURPOSE, OR NON-INFRINGEMENT.

7. Limitation of Liability

IN NO EVENT SHALL THE LICENSOR BE LIABLE FOR ANY DIRECT, INDIRECT, SPECIAL,
INCIDENTAL, OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES ARISING FROM THE USE OF THE SOURCE OR
PRODUCTS.

8. Termination

This Licence terminates automatically if You fail to comply with its terms.
Rights may be reinstated upon curing the violation.

9. Governing Law

This Licence is governed by the laws applicable at the Licensor’s place of
residence or principal place of business.

